			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style="margin-bottom: 0in;"><span style="font-weight: normal;">(<a href="http://www.emailwire.com/">EmailWire.Com</a>, February 01, 2009) Houston, TX - </span>In this segment of the GroupWeb Radio CEO Interview podcast ( <span style="color: #000080;"><span lang="zxx"><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="http://www.emailwire.com/podcast/">http://www.emailwire.com/podcast/</a></span></span></span> ), Dr. Marcia Yudkin, founder of PressReleaseHelp.com, talked about her more than two decades of helping clients get into the press and on the air.  Her first-ever press release lured several television crews to cover her group&#8217;s political demonstration, while her second landed her company on page one of the Wall Street Journal.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0in;">PressReleaseHelp.com offers a unique and cost-effective service, a press release makeover, which takes a so-so press release and transforms it into a well-written, newsworthy one.  Yudkin is the author of 6 Steps to Free Publicity, now in its third edition, as well as a home-study course called Deep Publicity, which teaches the secrets of non-stop newsworthiness.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0in;">Dr. Yudkin&#8217;s philosophy is that with creativity and discipline, any business, however small and ordinary, can generate endless publicity about its offerings.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0in;">For more information about PressReleaseHelp.com&#8217;s products and services, go to <span style="color: #000080;"><span lang="zxx"><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="http://www.pressreleasehelp.com/">http://www.pressreleasehelp.com</a></span></span></span> .</p>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0in;"><strong>About GroupWeb Radio CEO Interview Podcasting Service</strong></p>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0in;">Hosts of GroupWeb Radio, who are professional journalists, interview CEOs, business owners or managers about their products and services or causes. These interviews are published as podcasts and embedded in press releases that are distributed by EmailWire.Com throughout U.S. and global media outlets. See a clipping report of recent distributed podcast embeded in in press release: <span style="color: #000080;"><span lang="zxx"><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="http://www.emailwire.com/podcast/GroupWeb-Radio-Weekly-Podcast-Clipping-Report.php">http://www.emailwire.com/podcast/GroupWeb-Radio-Weekly-Podcast-Clipping-Report.php</a></span></span></span> . To schedule for an interview, go to <span style="color: #000080;"><span lang="zxx"><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="http://www.emailwire.com/podcast/">http://www.emailwire.com/podcast/</a></span></span></span> .</p>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0in;">
</p><p style="margin-bottom: 0in;"><span style="font-family: Verdana,sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: small;"><strong>About EmailWire.Com </strong></span></span></p>
